  "intro": "This quarter's list started as a simple ranking exercise: pull the 30 highest-performing creator-made TikToks about Pittsburgh small businesses by play count, cap representation at two videos per business so the survey stays wide, and see what the city is actually watching. The answer, across 198,450 total plays and 29 unique creators, is ice cream in Arlington, soup dumplings on the South Side, and a pastry case in Hazelwood. @bhphotographypa's visit to Page's Dairy Mart alone pulled 62,800 plays. @deluludayss turned Margaux in East Liberty into an aesthetic destination for 21,400 viewers who may have never heard of East Liberty before.\n\nThe detail that keeps surfacing as you move through the list: not one of these 18 businesses posted the video that put them on it. Every clip came from a customer, a local, a creator passing through. @melissasadhdlife filmed La Gourmandine. @bitesbymorgan filed the first Nan Xiang report. The businesses are being covered. They are not, for the most part, covering themselves.\n\nIssue 02 will look harder at why that gap exists, and what a few businesses are starting to do about it.",
